📘 Subject: General Studies Paper I (Prelims)
🧠 Topic: Towards Independence (1945–1947): Cabinet Mission, Mountbatten Plan & Partition

(Final stage of the Freedom Struggle.)

1️⃣ Core Teaching (Simple, Exam-Oriented)
🔹 Background

After World War II:

Britain weakened economically

Pressure from Indian national movement

INA trials increased nationalist sentiments

Naval Mutiny (1946) showed unrest in armed forces

📌 British realised they could not rule India longer.

🔵 Cabinet Mission Plan (1946)
Members:

Lord Pethick-Lawrence

Sir Stafford Cripps

A.V. Alexander

Objectives:

Transfer power peacefully

Avoid partition

Create federal structure

Key Proposals

Union of India with limited powers

Provinces grouped into 3 sections

Constituent Assembly to draft Constitution

📌 Congress accepted with reservations; Muslim League later rejected.

🔴 Direct Action Day (1946)

Called by Muslim League

Communal riots in Calcutta

Violence spread across India

📌 Increased demand for partition.

🔵 Mountbatten Plan (1947)
Announced by:

Lord Mountbatten (last Viceroy)

Key Decisions:

Partition of India & Pakistan

Transfer of power by August 1947

Provinces choose dominion

📌 Led to Indian Independence Act.

🔹 Indian Independence Act (1947)

Passed by British Parliament

India & Pakistan became independent dominions

End of British rule

📅 Independence: 15 August 1947

🔹 Consequences of Partition

Large-scale migration

Communal violence

Millions displaced

Creation of two nations

